parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden unintended acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
often when the brake pedal is depressed
the cruise control is engaged
or when shifting gears. The vehicle may surge forward
accelerate rapidly
or continue to move even when the brake pedal is applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty brake pedal design can cause the driver's foot to become lodged between the accelerator and brake pedals, leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: The driver's foot becomes stuck between the accelerator and brake pedals
making it difficult to brake or accelerate. The brake pedal cover may detach from the pedal itself.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cruise control malfunction can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: The cruise control fails to hold speed
accelerates unexpectedly
or does not disengage when the brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Interference between the accelerator and brake pedals can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: The accelerator and brake pedals are too close together
causing the driver's foot to accidentally press both pedals simultaneously.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to be difficult to steer, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the vehicle becomes hard to steer
the power steering assist suddenly malfunctions
the steering wheel sticks
the vehicle wanders while driving
the steering does not straighten out properly after turning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of steering components can cause the power steering system to fail, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: Rust or corrosion on the steering column
steering shaft
or other steering components
difficulty turning the steering wheel
the steering wheel sticks
the vehicle becomes hard to steer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the lower steering shaft assembly can cause the power steering system to fail, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: Difficulty turning the steering wheel
the vehicle becomes hard to steer
the power steering assist suddenly malfunctions
the steering wheel sticks
the vehicle wanders while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water accumulation inside the vehicle can cause electrical failures, damage to interior components, and create an unsafe driving environment.
symptoms: Water leaks into the passenger compartment
flooding the carpet
and creating a musty smell.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden shattering of the sunroof can cause injury, distraction, and loss of control while driving.
symptoms: Sunroof explodes or shatters without warning
often when opening or closing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Broken door handles can trap occupants inside the vehicle, creating a safety risk in emergency situations.
symptoms: Door handles break off
making it impossible to open the door from the inside.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The metal strip on the dashboard can cause a distorted glare, reducing visibility and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The metal strip on the dashboard reflects sunlight
creating a glare that obstructs the driver's view.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal Failure and Unintended Acceleration
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal and unintended acceleration can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities, as the vehicle may not stop or slow down as expected.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle surges forward when the brake is applied
the brake pedal is too close to the accelerator pedal
the vehicle accelerates unintentionally
the brake pedal has excessive free travel
the brake pedal is too close to the floorboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities, as the vehicle may not stop or slow down as expected.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle is involved in a collision
the brake system fails to function properly
the brake pedal has excessive free travel.
